                    Boundary Value Analysis
Boundary Value Analysis (BVA) is a software testing technique used to identify errors at the boundaries of input domains rather than within the range of valid input values.

Boundary Values:
Case	                Test Input	                    Expected Result
Below minimum            	17	                            Invalid
Minimum boundary	        18	                             Valid
Just above minimum	      19	                             Valid
Just below maximum	      59	                             Valid
Maximum boundary	        60	                             Valid
Above maximum	            61	                            Invalid


| Test Case ID            Test Scenario               Input (Age)           Expected Output                       Remarks
| ---------------- | --------------------------- | --------------- | ---------------------------------------- | -------------- |
| TC001            | Test below minimum age      | 17              | Error message: "Age must be 18 or above" | Negative test  |
| TC002            | Test minimum age            | 18              | Accepted                                 | Boundary value |
| TC003            | Test just above minimum age | 19              | Accepted                                 | Positive test  |
| TC004            | Test just below maximum age | 59              | Accepted                                 | Positive test  |
| TC005            | Test maximum age            | 60              | Accepted                                 | Boundary value |
| TC006            | Test above maximum age      | 61              | Error message: "Age must be 60 or below" | Negative test  |





